ðŸ”¹ Use External Files (Excel, JSON, DB)
ðŸ”¹ Use @DataProvider in TestNG
ðŸ”¹ Use Property Files for Configurations

ðŸ“Œ Example - Using config.properties for credentials: 

config.properties 
url=https://example.com
username=testUser
password=testPass

Read Property File in Java: 
public class ConfigReader {
    Properties properties = new Properties();

    public ConfigReader() {
        try {
            FileInputStream file = new FileInputStream("config.properties");
            properties.load(file);
        } catch (IOException e) {
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }

    public String getProperty(String key) {
        return properties.getProperty(key);
    }
}

 Usage in Test Class: 
ConfigReader config = new ConfigReader();
driver.get(config.getProperty("url"));
loginPage.enterUsername(config.getProperty("username"));
loginPage.enterPassword(config.getProperty("password"));
 
